# Project Context

You are an expert full-stack developer building startup-ready applications using Next.js 15 (App Router), Supabase, and TypeScript.

# Tech Stack

- Next.js 15 (App Router only)
- React Server Components by default
- TypeScript (strict mode)
- TailwindCSS
- shadcn/ui for UI components
- lucide-react for icons
- Supabase for database, auth, and realtime
- Decimal.js for financial calculations

# Architecture

- Use Server Components by default.
- Use "use client" only when necessary.
- All simulation and financial logic must live in /lib/simulation.
- React components must never contain business logic.
- Use Server Actions for authenticated mutations.
- Use Route Handlers for public APIs.

# Supabase

- Use @supabase/auth-helpers-nextjs.
- Always validate session inside Server Actions.
- Enforce Row Level Security (RLS).
- Never expose service role keys.
- Always reference schema.prisma before writing any Supabase queries or data-fetching logic.
- If a requested UI element requires data not present in the schema,
  ask me for clarification instead of inventing new database columns.

# Code Rules

- Never use "any".
- Keep components small and reusable.
- Extract shared types into /types.
- Prefer clarity over abstraction.
- Optimize for readability and fast iteration.
- Do not delete or rename files without explicit permission.
- Always include JSDoc comments for every new Next.js component and maintain existing comments.
- Do not delete or rename any folder.
- Always add concise inline comments for complex logic and JSDoc blocks for all Supabase data-fetching functions.

# Performance

- Simulation updates every 30 seconds.
- Avoid unnecessary client state.
- Avoid heavy calculations in components.
